Chapt1
OSI MODEL (7 layer): Representation of how network work
Scope: Basic Local Area Network

Ethernet Frame: travels through each individual system. (think of it as register that need decoding)
Consist of: Preamble, SFD, SRCE/DEST MAC ADDR, ETHER type/length, payload data, FCS

Layers

Physical(1) 
 - Deal with specific hardware/device
 - Act as Network Card: Takes Preamble from EF. EF act as warning sign and warns Network card of an incoming frame
 - Takes FCS from frame and check if the data that was sent is same as it receive. 
 - Remove FCS and Preamble from frame

Data Link(2)
 - Check if the EF is addressed for Data Link base on Mac Address (unique 48 bit value in every network card wireless or wired)
 - look at Destination MAC address in EF and compare with Datalink address
 - Delete EF if address doesn't match
 - MAC Address: Physical address burned into every network card(use for local area network)
 - Destination MAC comes with Source MAC and can be use to sent it back to sender. (Doesn't delete)
 - IP PACKET: EF with Dest/SRCE MAC and previous parts remove


Network(3)
 - Look at IP addresses. (used for large distributed network such as internet)
 - Process similar to data link. (SRCE/DEST IP address)


Transport(4)
 - Assemble and disassemble different pieces of data
 - Data is generally big. (each EF can only holds 1500 bytes of data)
 - Send huge data and chop the data into chunks(1500 byte chunk) or reassemble chunks into one whole

Session(5)
 - Establish connection between current host to another host. (ex: employee & client email)
 - if the IP address is in the right computer, the port number (in packet) gets the data into right application
 - Grabs SRCE/DEST Port number


Presentation(6)
 - Check if the data gets to the right application but also check if data is in correct format that the application can view
 - Isn't significant currently since applications now are able to read every different format of data.

Application(7)
 -  Built in application interface or API. Gives ability to talk to other network. 

